# API Client & Auth Patterns

## API client (`src/api/client.js`)

### Adding a new endpoint
1. Add the function to `client.js`:

```javascript
export async function fetchNewThing(params) {
  const qs = new URLSearchParams(params).toString();
  return apiFetch(`/new-thing/?${qs}`);
}
```

2. For authenticated endpoints, `apiFetch` auto-handles JWT tokens
3. For POST/PATCH/DELETE, pass `method` and `body`:

```javascript
export async function createNewThing(data) {
  return apiFetch('/new-thing/', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify(data),
  });
}
```

### Token lifecycle
- Tokens stored in `localStorage` under key `delta_tokens`
- On 401 response, `apiFetch` auto-refreshes using the refresh token
- If refresh fails, user is logged out (tokens cleared)
- `isLoggedIn()` checks if tokens exist (does not validate them)

## AuthContext (`src/context/AuthContext.jsx`)

### Available from `useAuth()`
| Field/Fn       | Type     | Notes                         |
|---------------|----------|-------------------------------|
| `user`        | object   | `null` when not authenticated |
| `loading`     | boolean  | `true` during initial check   |
| `loginUser`   | fn       | `(username, password) => Promise` |
| `registerUser`| fn       | `(username, email, password) => Promise` |
| `logoutUser`  | fn       | Clears tokens and user state  |

### Auth guard pattern
- Never block content behind auth — content is always public
- Use `if (!user) return null` to hide auth-only UI elements
- Show a "Sign In" prompt instead of hiding features completely

## Environment variables
- `VITE_API_URL` — backend base URL (default: `http://localhost:8000/api`)
- Set in `.env` locally or in Netlify deploy settings for production
